BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:American Made: Paintings and Sculpture from the DeMell Jacobsen Co
 llection
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20261015T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20270124T235959
UID:10001925-1792022400-1800835199@www.taubmanmuseum.org
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads
 /2026/01/web-John-Singer-Sargent_Portrait-of-Elsie-Wagg.jpg
DESCRIPTION:American Made: Paintings and Sculpture from the DeMell Jacobse
 n Collection features more than 100 works of art by renowned American arti
 sts such as John Singer Sargent\, Elizabeth Catlett\, Mary Cassatt\, Rober
 t Henri\, Sarah Miriam Peale\, Thomas Cole\, and Charles Alston\, among ot
 hers.\n\nDrawn entirely from the DeMell Jacobsen Collection\, the exhibiti
 on beautifully surveys the distinctive styles and thought-provoking art cr
 eated by American artists over the past two centuries.\n\nThough many obje
 cts from the DeMell Jacobsen Collection have been on view at other museums
 \, ranging from the Metropolitan Museum of Art to the Smithsonian American
  Art Museum\, this is the first exhibition to bring the best of the collec
 tion together in one location.\n\nThe exhibition begins with portraits by 
 masters including Rembrandt Peale and Thomas Sully before moving on to hig
 hlight the development of mid-19th-century landscape painting with works b
 y Asher B. Durand\, John Frederick Kensett\, and others.\n\nEnticing image
 s of fruits\, flowers\, and other delights by Severin Roesen\, John Franci
 s\, Ferdinand Richardt\, Elizabeth Williams\, and Adelaide Coburne Palmer 
 are featured alongside trompe l’oeil examples by William Michael Harnett
 \, John Haberle\, and John Peto.\n\nTwentieth-century modernism and realis
 m can be seen in works by artists ranging from Patrick Henry Bruce and Mar
 sden Hartley to Paul Cadmus\, Charmion von Wiegand\, Suzy Frelinghuysen\, 
 Elizabeth Catlett\, and Ernie Barnes.\n\nThe mission of the Thomas H. and 
 Diane DeMell Jacobsen Ph.D. Foundation to “carefully research and obtain
  American masterpieces” is abundantly represented in American Made .\n\n
 American Made was curated by Todd Herman\, PhD\, President and CEO of The 
 Mint Museum\; Kevin Sharp\, Director of the Dixon Gallery and Gardens\; an
 d Jonathan Stuhlman\, PhD\, Senior Curator of American Art at The Mint Mus
 eum.\n\nThis exhibition is on view October 15\, 2026-January 24\, 2027\, w
 ith an Opening Celebration on Saturday\, October 10\, and Member Preview D
 ay October 11.\n\nCheck back soon for tickets!\n\nSource: https://www.taub
 manmuseum.org/american-made
